                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12853560" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 5 Apr 2010 22:16:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh geez my bad. I wanted to lower the value that makes us print out the message but I didn&apos;t think about the master with long running sleeps. I guess we need to go back to a multiplier.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12853588" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 5 Apr 2010 23:02:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The condition to print the message is now 2 times the sleep period. I&apos;m also adding the time we should have slept. Sounds good?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12853599" author="stack" created="Mon, 5 Apr 2010 23:32:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;J-D and I chatted.  2x is too little if sleep of one second.  He&apos;s going to add minimum of ten seconds and 2x (10 second GC pause is worth noting).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12853601" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 5 Apr 2010 23:41:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed to branch and trunk a fix that checks for a delta of 10 seconds between the time slept and the period.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12866843" author="stack" created="Wed, 12 May 2010 23:52:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking these as fixed against 0.21.0 rather than against 0.20.5.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017542" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:43:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
